<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by greywolffe on 04-23-2001 02:34 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Yes, I think they should have a way to improve Tunare faction, but as stated earlier it should be quite difficult.

How about this:

High Priest of Tunare:  You wish to gain favor with Our Lady?  Well to do this you must show your faith and devotion by accomplishing a small task.  Go to the heart of the Dark Elven city.  Find the blasphemous clerics guild.  Inside you must recover a crystal that was stolen from one of our smaller sanctums and return it to me.

Ok, now you have to first get to the clerics of Felwithe to receive this quest.  Hmmm, since you're kos you'll need a disguise.  Wolf form comes to mind (so find a druid) and zone into Felwithe.  Oops, forgot, wolf form drops when you zone, so have your druid friend zone in first.  Should be easy getting to the priest from here.

Now head out to the DE city (forget its name..sorry).  Getting past the newbie guards in wolf form should be easy right?  Have your druid friend zone in first as in Felwithe.  Oops forgot about the guards close to the inside zone.  You may be able to fight them off, maybe not.  After that it's wolf form again (are wolves KOS in this city?)

You find the guild, you locate the crystal and you get out.  Once you get back to the Felwithe priest you are rewarded with the following:

Increased faction to Priests of Tunare (+1)
Increased faction to Tunarian Court (+1)

Since you're already down say -2500 this should cover the "difficult" part of regaining faction as it will take you a long time to repair it.  KEEP in mind though, that it "IS" repairable in this scenario.

I just think it should be fixable, no matter how dedious or repetative (like that's new to eq).



------------------
Greywolffe Silverstarr
52nd Cleric of Tunare
E'Marr</TEXTAREA>
